Actress Heather Locklear arrested for driving under the influence of drugs
Actress Heather Locklear, the popular Amanda from Melrose Place, was arrested this weekend in Santa Barbara, California for driving under the influence of drugs.
A witness saw her perform unusual maneuvers as she tried to pull out of a parking lot in Montecito, a spokesman for the California Highway Patrol told People magazine.
The witness said that at about 4.30 p.m., Locklear "took a sharp step on the gas, moved forwards and backwards in a loud rumble, and tried to leave the parking space - she turned on her sunglasses several times while reversing".
The witness, who apparently did not recognize the actress at first, saw Locklear moments after she stopped on a nearby highway and stepped out of the vehicle.
This person also alerted the emergency services because "she was worried about Locklear's life".
When a police patrol arrived at the scene, she found the actress inside the vehicle, which partially blocked the roadway.
"She looked disoriented", so the officers took her to a specialized drug and alcohol center to undergo a test.
