According to statistics, between 30 and 75% of motorists accused of drunk driving more than once will get back behind the wheel in this state.
Alcolock should prevent this, as it is a system connected to the vehicle that measures the level of alcohol in the exhaled air and prevents the car from starting if the driver does not breathe before or if a higher than permitted concentration of alcohol is recorded.
Its price exceeds 1,000 euros and it would have to be paid by the culprit himself.
A study to this effect in the USA in 2007 showed that infractions were reduced by 65% in the first year after introduction for vehicles equipped with this equipment.
In Spain, it is estimated that 115 people could be saved each year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to address this behaviour before it results in a criminal offence.
